    "To make a prediction, the user must send their data to the cloud to receive the inference results (Lakhan et al. 2021).",
    "Consequently, user data could be compromised, leading to the exposure of private data.",
    "In general, TEE can be used in the ML inference phase in the cloud.",
    "However, the current widely used ML and DL models could be computationally intensive for the regular environment.",
    "The computational load for the same operation in TEEs is significantly larger than in an untrusted environment with increasing execution time and latency."
